## üöÄ What is Aura?

Aura is a **natural language programming language** that lets you build web applications using plain English commands. No more memorizing syntax‚Äîjust write what you want, and Aura's AI Brain autocorrects it for you.

```aura
Create a heading with the text 'Welcome to My App'
Create a button with the text 'Click Me'
When clicked, display 'Hello World!'
```

**That's it.** Aura transpiles this into a production-ready React app with Tailwind CSS.

---

## ‚ú® Features

### üß† **AI-Powered Autocorrection**
Type naturally, make typos‚ÄîAura Brain fixes them in real-time.
```aura
crete a butn with text 'Submit'  ‚Üí  Create a button with the text 'Submit'
```

### ‚ö° **Lightning Fast**
- **100-300ms** autocorrection (2-5x faster than traditional transpilers)
- **Live watch mode** rebuilds on save
- **Hot reload** for instant preview

### üé® **Beautiful by Default**
- Modern UI with Tailwind CSS
- Dark mode support
- Responsive layouts
- Premium components (cards, navbars, forms)

### üîß **Developer Friendly**
- VS Code extension with IntelliSense
- Real-time error highlighting
- Comprehensive documentation
- Active community support

---

## üì¶ Installation

### Quick Install (Recommended)

```bash
# Install from PyPI
pip install aura-lang

# Verify installation
aura --version
```

That's it! You're ready to create your first Aura project.

### Install from Source

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/kingenious0/Aura-Programming-Language.git
cd Aura-Programming-Language

# Install in editable mode
pip install -e .
```

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.8+
- Node.js 16+ (auto-installed during `aura init`)


---

## üéØ Quick Start

### 1. Create a New Project

```bash
# Create project folder
mkdir my-app
cd my-app

# Initialize Aura project (creates structure, downloads AI, sets up React/Vite)
aura init
```

**Output:**
```
============================================================
  üöÄ AURA PROJECT INITIALIZER
============================================================
  Creating professional structure...
  ‚úì Created pages/, assets/, components/
  ‚úì Generated sample files
  ‚úì Aura Brain ready
  ‚úì React/Vite engine initialized
============================================================
  ‚úÖ PROJECT INITIALIZED SUCCESSFULLY!
============================================================
```

### 2. Start Developing

```bash
# Start hot-reload dev server
aura dev
```

Your app is now running at `http://localhost:5173`! üöÄ

### 3. Add Pages

```bash
# Create a new page (while dev server is running)
cd pages
echo "Create a heading with the text 'Products'" > Products.aura
```

**Boom!** Page is instantly live at `/products` (no restart needed!)

---

## ‚ö° The Aura Advantage

### **React/Vite Way** (30+ minutes)

```bash
npm create vite@latest my-app
cd my-app
npm install
npm install react-router-dom tailwindcss
# Configure Tailwind...
# Create folder structure...
# Write boilerplate...
# Configure routing...
npm run dev
```

### **Aura Way** (2 minutes)

```bash
mkdir my-app
cd my-app
aura init
aura dev
```

**10x faster setup. 100x simpler code.** ‚ú®

